  <div id="hdb" class="scroll-mt-40">
    <DefBox
      term="Keeping a Chihuahua in an HDB flat"
      definition="The Chihuahua is named on the HDB-approved breed list, so you can keep one in an HDB flat. HDB allows one dog of an approved breed per flat, and at 1.5 to 3 kg the Chihuahua sits further inside the small-breed rules than any other dog. Every Chihuahua we place has its dog licensing completed at purchase, so the paperwork is handled for you."
      bridge="Is a Chihuahua HDB-approved? Yes, by name on the list. Just mind the one-dog-per-flat rule, and if you already have a dog, message us first so we can check your situation."
      citationLabel="Read HDB's guidelines on keeping pets"
      citationHref="https://www.hdb.gov.sg/managing-my-home/home-ownership/keeping-pets"
